N:marketing-automation
D:Route broad product and growth marketing asks into one KPI-aware brief, one chosen lane, and one implementation-ready packet across CRO, copy, SEO, analytics, pricing, launch, retention, and experiments.
G:marketing|growth|cro|copywriting|seo|analytics|pricing|launch|retention|experiments|routing
F:Claude|ChatGPT|Gemini|Codex

U[5]:
  Turn a messy marketing request into a structured routing brief
  Choose one primary lane across CRO, messaging, SEO/content, ads/analytics, or strategy/growth
  Produce one implementation-ready packet instead of channel soup
  Add explicit KPI, assumptions, next artifact, and measurement logic
  Route narrow specialist or game-store launch work outward when needed

S[5]{n,action,details}:
  1,Normalize,Capture objective primary_kpi audience surface offer constraints and main_question in a lightweight marketing_brief
  2,ChooseLane,Pick exactly one lane that reduces ambiguity fastest and name any secondary handoff separately
  3,BuildPacket,Return one routing brief channel-ready brief copy packet measurement packet or launch/growth brief
  4,AddMeasurement,Include assumptions success thresholds and what to measure after implementation
  5,RouteOut,Escalate specialist work such as Steam store launch ops instead of absorbing everything into general marketing

R[4]:
  One primary KPI and one primary lane per packet
  Prefer explicit assumptions over blocking on missing detail
  Keep broad routing distinct from narrow specialist execution
  Always name the next artifact and how success will be measured

E[2]{desc,in,out}:
  "Broad launch ask","We are launching a new SaaS workflow next month and need help with messaging, landing page copy, onboarding emails, and how to measure whether it worked.","Marketing Routing Brief with one primary lane, launch/growth packet, assumptions, secondary handoff, and measurement checklist"
  "Landing page conversion ask","Our homepage gets traffic but signups are flat. Help with conversion.","Marketing Routing Brief with CRO lane, prioritized decisions, immediate next steps, and experiment/measurement checklist"
